  <info type="description">
    <p>"A world file is a six line plain text sidecar file used by geographic information systems
      (GIS) to georeference raster map images. The file specification was introduced by Esri,
      and consists of six coefficients of an affine transformation that describes the location,
      scale and rotation of a raster on a map." (Wikipedia)</p>
